            <dateline>65 Park Road, <lb/>West Dulwich, London.<lb/>5 June 1884</dateline>
            <opener>My dear Sir,</opener>
            <p>I have heard from D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>.. Bower of Madras in reply to my request for information about Indo-Portuguese He says the use of the language has nearly disappeared in <placeName ref="[authorityLink]">
Madras</placeName>. He sends the only book he could obtain, which I have the pleasure of sending you herewith.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Yrs sincerely,</salute>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">R. Caldwell</persName>, Bishop. </signed>
            </closer>
